{{Infobox OS |name = Anonym.OS |screenshot = [[Image:anonymos screenshot.jpg|250px]] |caption = A screenshot of Anonym.OS Beta 4 |developer = [http://kaos.to/cms/ kaos.theory] |family = [[OpenBSD]] |source_model = [[Open source]] |latest_release_version = Beta 4 |latest_release_date = January 14, 2006 |kernel_type = [[Monolithic kernel|Monolithic]] |licence = Mostly [[BSD license|BSD]] |working_state = Unmaintained |website = [http://sourceforge.net/projects/anonym-os/ www.sourceforge.net] }} '''Anonym.OS''' was a [[Live CD]] [[operating system]] based on [[OpenBSD]] 3.8 with strong [[encryption]] and anonymization tools. The goal of the project was to provide a secure anonymous [[internet|web browsing]] access to everyday users.<ref name=Wired> {{cite web |url=http://www.wired.com/news/technology/internet/0,70017-0.html?tw=wn_tophead_1 |title=Anonyity on a Disc|publisher=[[Wired.com]] |date=January 14, 2006|author=Quinn Norton |accessdate=November 6, 2011}} </ref> The operating system was [[OpenBSD]] 3.8, although many [[Software package (installation)|packages]] have been added to facilitate its goal. It used [[Fluxbox]] as its [[window manager]].
The project was discontinued after the release of Beta 4. <ref> {{cite web |url=http://distrowatch.com/table.php?distribution=anonymos |title=Anonym.OS LiveCD |publisher=[[DistroWatch]] |accessdate=November 6, 2011}}</ref>
